Kerr Spacetime Geodesic Generator documentation (WIP)

Dependencies:
pypy (optional)
matplotlib
vpython


Sample usage:

Run and plot one of the initial conditions files:

./rungraphics ic/CircleUnStable


Generate initial conditions to stdout:

./genparam.py 11.5 12.5 0.45 1.0 1.0

(PARAMETERS: min r, max r, max theta, spin, Lz multiplier)


Generate, run, and plot geodesic

./genparam.py 11.5 12.5 0.45 1.0 1.0 >test 2>potential; ./rungraphics test


Take every 1000th point of geodesic data and pass to David Madore's kerr-image raytracer (ftp://ftp.madore.org/pub/madore/misc/kerr-image.c)

./raytrace.py 1000 <data | ./raytrace [PATH-TO-KERR-IMAGE]



Particle trajectories

http://staff.science.nus.edu.sg/~phylyk/downloads/reports/sp2172_report.pdf

Light trajectories

http://www.physics.nus.edu.sg/~phyteoe/kerr/paper.pdf

